reviews_data.review_text: the worst service I've ever seen!!

Roomy, and comfortable setting. The cashier had mistaken my order for jasmine green tea for milk tea. He quickly made up for it and even gave me the milk tea on the house! Truly great customer service! Definitely will be back for more!
Amazing service, great workers. Overall 5 star. Love this place so much.

Tucked in a shopping mall near the Charlotte Premium outlets, Ding Tea is my new bubble tea spot. Drinks are customizable. If you are unsure of what to order Ding Teas list their most popular teas on one of their boards. The employees are helpful and always friendly. Oh... and their photo op area is just the cutest!

By far, Ding Tea is one of the best bubble tea establishments!

The “thai tea” tastes like straight milk. It has no flavor whatsoever. I used to really like this place because it’s a 5-minute drive but they’re not as good as before and the girls working there are rude and not welcoming at all.

My students wanted a boba party as their reward and this place accommodated for the big order, gave me a great discount, helped me carry the order to my car (in the rain), and were just fantastic in communicating! My students loved it and I definitely did too!
reviews_data.owner_answer: No problem! thank you for catering with us

reviews_data.review_text: the drinks aren’t as good as before, the employees are always looking upset/annoyed. But that one girl named Marie, is always kind, helpful, and positive.
Used to be so good, now it’s just watery. What happens to this place?
Horrible service! They don’t greet you, or make you feel welcomed. Traveling from Virginia and the experience was horrible. Will not be coming back

I like it here. Drinks are good and staff is usually friendly.

Only downside is that it always smells very strongly of cleaning chemicals
MONSTER. BOBA. LATTE. That is all 🫶 Plus it’s one of the few boba places that deliver in 15 min or less (a lot average 40-50 min just for some tea!!)
Very peaceful and beautiful inside! Great boba as well
Great service and clean energy also nice bathroom. Brown Sugar tea is my favorite.

Atmosphere: I wish the inside was colder. It's not uncomfortably warm but wish it was cool inside.
Food: ordered classic milk tea. **Ding Tea does not come with tapioca pearls as default. You must order it extra. Wish the tapioca balls were softer and chewier.

The boba is usually pretty good and the place is always clean but 9 times out of 10 they do not have boba. I will never understand how a BOBA CAFE does not have boba. Almost every time I go, they say they don’t have any boba. They have the tea but no boba. This is the most disappointing part about the whole place ok top of the servers not being at all happy to help customers. Once in a blue moon when they have boba, it’s quite good, otherwise this place is disappointing. Better spend your boba money elsewhere.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Alisia thank you for your review. We will work on having the boba in stock. During peak times we will be sold out. We try to cook the perfect amount to keep them on being fresh and always cook new ones every 3 hours.

reviews_data.review_text: I was there for a boba milk tea. Finally I found they serve honeydew milk tea. Requested them to make it extra sweet and extra tapioca. It was awesome.

Ok, so I had never been here before and wanted to stop by and see if they had Vietnamese coffee (they do not).  Walked in and was not busy at all, so the girl behind the counter immediately greeted us and was just waiting for us to order. Now she was just standing there waiting and that makes me nervous so I quickly just tried to order some forms of coffee drink. I ended up ordering a large Vanilla flavored coffee drink and a Chai tea. Now the Boba balls do not come with the drink, that is extra (which is weird bc usually those drinks come with it). I didnt realize until after I ordered that you can tell them how much ice you want and also the sugar level you would like in your drink (extra, normal, less, slightly...etc) so unfortunately I DID not like my drink at all. I wish I could have just taken the time out to look through the menu or all of the signs they had taped with all the information to help you order. Also, I feel like the girl behind the counter could've helped me out or explained things better as she did see me get flustered and I asked questions but she looked rather annoyed that I didn't know what to order. Idk I may return, but not in a rush.
El servicio es horrible y muy grosero, pedí un tea de boba y estaba asqueroso, los sorbetes se rompían nunca entren a este lugar
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Arturo,
Please contact us at dingteanc@gmail.com we want to make this right with you.  We are looking into changing the straws as they break easy. Hope to hear back from you.

reviews_data.review_text: Servicio 0. Mala atención y el boba tea asqueroso, no sabia a mango que era el sabor que queria, perdi mi dinero en este lugar no pude ni tomar esa bebida
wonderful customer service. Great BOBA
I love this

I wish the cashier would've been enthusiastic to want to help us, instead of making us feel stupid for not knowing what was inside the drinks. The Boba shop on Cherry Rd, in Rock Hill, was more happy to recommend to us drinks and tell us what was inside the drinks. The Rock Hill one actually helped us and asked us how we liked the drink and helped us customize our drinks to our liking. But inside here, the girl made me feel dumb for not knowing the drinks from THIS specific location, which I let her know that it was our first time here. She proceeded with her faces. As soon as we were done with ordering, she left the register and sat down with another female on their computers. I won't be coming back.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Ana, can you please email us at Dingteanc@gmail.com. We apologize for this and hope to make this right.

reviews_data.review_text: The boba tea is always delicious whenever I stop in. The staff are nice, but don't always greet you. The store is clean and bright! The only real downside is, I'm not sure what air freshener or cleaner they are using, but it's always so strong when I go in and I can't wait to get my drink and leave.

reviews_data.review_text: The vanilla Boba tea is my favorite
The Thai tea taste nothing close to Thai tea flavor, very disappointed in that.
My favorite place for boba!!
Never a disappointment at ding tea. I got my usual, monster latte. Delicious .  I also tried a new drink I haven't had before. Lychee with aloe Vera. It was very refreshing, perfect for a hot day.

This review is overdue. I stopped by for the first time on Tuesday, 12-13-22. Had just finished a pedicure. It was cold and I wanted a hot drink. I ordered a milk tea; think brown sugar. It was ok. Was hot but not too hot to drink right away while I was driving to run an errand.

Very cute and quaint place to go and enjoy a nice drink. I got mine to go since I was in a rush, but I got the monster boba latte and it was absolutely delish and refreshing. I would certainly go back and maybe take the time to sit and read a book while enjoying a nice drink.
Just when I was having a bad week, you ladies ROCK! I needed this message! I'm a regular Herr and Jasmine Milk Tea with golden Boba for the WIN! STAY beautiful ladies!
Never left a review in my life, but the Jasmine Milk Tea made me do it.  Good spot to visit with friends and plenty of other nearby shops to keep you entertained while you sip.
Very poor customer service! Can't even greet your customer or have a smile! Smh, then don't work here.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Dilora, sorry to hear about your experience. Will bring to attention this issue to make aware and better the customer service experience.

reviews_data.review_text:
Amazing tea & options. Love, to be able customize the sweetness & ice!!!
Maybe one more cashier & it would be perfect! Great job, keep it up!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Coffee Jelly, Aloe Vera, Lychee Jelly

reviews_data.review_text: I love my coffee and decided to try Ding Teas brown sugar coffee. I am not disappointed! The vibe is truly lovely and the service was very friendly! 10/10 recommend, will be back!
Don't listen to Alejandra Guzman I'm short and dark skinned and I love going here. They attend me Immediately and they give the absolute best customer service. Highly recommend!! I'm a female btw :3

I’ve been coming to this place since last summer! and I’ve never had anything bad to say about this until today! I walked in and every one from their staff like all the girls there saw me walked in and just stared at me, not even a Hello! Or welcome! Or we’ll be right with you. I was not even acknowledged, then when I noticed one girl came to register I walked up to her and she kept staring at me not saying a word, so after silent was so uncomfortable then I immediately asked for my order, and paid for it. As I’m putting my PIN number, a guy walks in and the girl with blond hair immediately welcomed him ask how he’s doing and what he needed, but me because I’m a girl they treated like trash. I would never ever! Come back to this place, they are so disrespectful immature, this people represent and are the face of your business, so in order to keep customers they should be nice and create a nice welcoming environment so customers will come back. I guess I have to be dark, tall and a guy for me to be acknowledged and welcome to this business. You should re-evaluate your staff because if they did that to me, I can only imagine how rude they are to others. If I could give a -0 I would.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Alejandra, I am sorry for your experience. Please email dingteanc@gmail.com to help resolve this issue. We hope to see you again

reviews_data.review_text: Gorgeous drink/ hang-out spot and the drinks are delicious. You have to try the bubble tea. However, there’s no public restrooms. But, there are spots around Ding Tea that have public restrooms for you.
Put in an order for pick up. Added extra golden boba cuz theirs is so tasty (but sweet, so you might order a lower sugar level with them). It was so tasty and fast! Workers were super kind.

Ding tea on Independence！Love the big sign that says Taiwanese tea shop. This shop is bigger than it looks on the outside. Clean, airy and bright. Last time I had Ding tea is at their Shopton location, I have to say their tea at least have tea flavors and the boba are pretty chewy, I just didn’t like the creamer too overpowering the tea. That’s just me though my daughter thinks it’s pretty good! Support small business.
The boba  was so good and the cashier person was very nice and patient with me and my son and daughter and the store was very pretty and the decor was nice and aesthetic.
I ordered the Signature Milk Tea, Hokkaido Coffee(with Almond milk), Mango Slush 🥭 Everything was good :)

Employees are always nice, very friendly and welcoming girls! ^_^
Drinks are freshly made always and the music is upbeat! My #1 boba drink go to!
Rewards system is great too!
Ordered passion fruit green tea with mango popping boba which was great! Mango slush with strawberry popping boba tastes a little off but not bad. The place is very cute inside, nice selfie wall 🎉

It was very nice on the inside and there were only 3 staff members . No one else was inside and the interaction was a little awkward at the register considering it was my first time going. The person making my drink kept going to the back with my drink though so I thought that was kinda weird. Could just be paranoid tho lol. Pretty ok place 👍🏽
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi thank you for your review! Near the end of the shift the ice and tea in the front will run low so they will have to replenish it in the back and Boil more tea.

reviews_data.review_text: Love this place!!!
Not impressed! The tea was very bland and bubble wasn't fresh. Doesn't teast like good quality at all.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Kexin,
We are sorry about your experience and hope to make it up to you. Please email Dingteanc@gmail.com and can make it up to you. At Ding Tea we are brewing fresh Tea and Bubble multiple times throughout the day. Some properties that could affect the flavor of the tea is including 0% ice which would dilute the flavoring of sweeter because we add more tea base onto the drink.

reviews_data.review_text: Ding is the best boba in Charlotte hands down !!
One of  my fav best place to get bubble tea in Charlotte
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much Claudia for the continued support!

reviews_data.review_text: I love bubble tea and it was my first time there. Ordered Matcha Milk Tea and it was so refreshing since I was thirsty!
I always love coming here. It's my go-to spot for bubble tea.
Best place for boba. Easy to customize order and always fresh
Discovered it while shoping near the Asian market. Love that monster boba latte!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Glad you love it! thank you so much

reviews_data.review_text: Definitely the best boba in Charlotte. Friendly staffs!!!!
Wonderful place to get boba tea in Charlotte area. Definitely going back here again to grab my boba drink
I love this place! It has such a clean and professional atmosphere. The staff are all so welcoming and if it’s your first time drinking Boba, the staff do very well at explaining every drink.

The person taking my order left their AirPods in and left me having to repeat my order several times. First they were about to ring up a completely different drink, they thought I wanted STRAWBERRY when I ordered wintermelon, as if those two words sound the same. I corrected them and thought it was okay after that, then I got some kind of yellow boba in my drink even though I asked them for black boba. I asked them why they put it in my drink suspecting they misheard me yet again from STILL NOT TAKING THE AIRPODS OUT and they told me “It tastes the same.” It did not taste the same, it had like a grassy, honey kind of taste. I saw they even had black boba out on the counter so it’s not even like they ran out. No offer to remake my drink or anything, I was so fed up. I’d rather keep buying boba from inside G-Mart. I’m giving two stars because the decor is SUPER PRETTY and I like the ambiance, for that reason alone I’ll likely try it again someday and update my review.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello Sydney I am so sorry for your experience. Will let the staff know about this incident so it will not happen again. Currently we only have in stock Golden Boba with brown sugar, we do not serve black boba at this moment but will in the future. Hope to serve you again in the future and bring satisfaction next time

reviews_data.review_text: best tea in Charlotte, cant go wrong here
I loved my passion fruit green tea!
Their boba teas are the best in Charlotte hands down. Glad to have a new boba shop near Matthews area!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your feed back and support!

reviews_data.review_text: Wow wow wow!! So delicious. I got the Monster Boba Latte recommended by one of the staff and it is soooo so good. The employees here were so kind and attentive! Very engaging and creating such an overall lovely environment. The place was so cute inside as well!!! Such a great little hidden gem off of independence. Great job guys!! 💕
An ok place to get bubble tea.

Took the family here for dessert and left satisfied 👍🏼😁. There is a flavor for everyone, whether its the Lychee slush when im feeling fruity or the monster boba latte when im sweet😫. They are new to the area of course they are going to be their best behavior, go check them out for yourselves!
Very good quality bubble tea and fast, friendly service. In contention for the best bubble tea spot in Charlotte
Def recommend!! Friendly staff and delicious drinks!!!!!
I love the Signature Milk Tea! Decorations are so pretty, great for pictures
They are remarkable! Been here every time I’ve visited Charlotte, they have SO MANY options to choose from and I loved them all, will definitely come again!
amazing drinks and amazing customer service !! 🤩🤩
FIRST TIME HAVING BOBA, IM IMPRESSED… Amazing customer service, the restaurant has an amazing feel and aesthetic, workers are so nice and caring. I give it 10/10
This place is precious. The people are kind, it is so clean and it's delicious!
One of the best boba shops in Charlotte!!! Really great service and awesome atmosphere!!!

I just want to say this place is amazing. I have never been in a tea house before. I like what they are serving 😍 so many amazing tea combinations I'll be back. So today I purchased the Monster Boba latte so good.
great service and a very clean and organized place ! the drinks are also VERY good
The service was really nice and fast
Very friendly staff, I loved the environment and drinks as well. Will definitely be coming here more
Very good boba, i love the thai milk tea with sea cream, always very good
I personally love coming here after work, the drinks are very consistent and tasty. One of the better tea shops around!
Stopped by here when I was in Charlotte. Very great and delicious boba!
I really love the boba there. The workers are very friendly and the place is very cute. I will recommend this place.
One of my favorite boba spots in Charlotte! Friendly staff, and there’s a lot to choose from their menu.
The matcha creama 10/10 highly recommend! And the staffs are super friendly!
Super clean and very friendly staff. Best boba place in Charlotte!
Bought myself a aloe vera kiwi with rainbow jelly juice. So good. Staff are friendly. Definitely recommend this place 😁
First time going. They were so sweet to help me, I loved my drink
I had the ginger milk tea with coffee jelly. It was very tasty.
I moved to Charlotte from ATL and this is my boba spot. I’ve been to a hand full in Charlotte and this one is the best. The drink is always perfect and everyone here is helpful.
The boba Tea is so amazing! the signature milk Tea had strong black tea flavor and amazing staff
Best boba tea in Charlotte
Taro milk tea! Yummmmm

I bought the strawberry milk tea with strawberry jelly and I can positively say that as soon as I took a sip, I was amazed. The jelly was so good and they use a syrup on the side of the cup that really does taste like strawberry. My sister got the yakult/strawberry slush and said it was amazing! We both enjoyed it so much, we definitely will be back!

We got the kiwi slush, brown sugar milk tea, and strawberry yakult slush all with boba. All of them were great! The workers were friendly and I didn't have to wait long at all. Will definitely be coming back to try some other stuff.
The Taro Milk Tea is the best here!!! I also really like their Monster Boba Latte!
reviews_data.owner_answer: thanks so much!

reviews_data.review_text: Came here for the first time and they got one of our orders wrong. We ordered a wintermelon milk green tea but the drink tasted 100% like Thai tea. We didn't catch this until we already left so we couldn't say anything. It was the strangest thing bc how do you mess up an entire drink??
Such great people working there! And love the fact you can customize your teas! So clean and fast.
Absolutely delicious!! We tried the Strawberry Slush and the Monster Boba; by far the best we have ever had!! The shop is adorable and the workers are so kind! We will definitely be back soon!
Great bubble tea! Their royal milk tea is the best
super nice and welcoming! This is my second day in a row visiting!

Had a good experience. I like trying out places and this wasn't a bad one! So pretty and clean. They just opened up but I know a lot of people will stop in. I had a oolong tea with milk and Boba. It was not to milky that it would take away from flavor. Just right! Staff was fun and had Hospitality which is 🔑. Will be back soon when I go shopping in the area!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much!

reviews_data.review_text: My fav boba place😍😍😍
Customer service is extremely polite and helpful.
Staff is Very Nice and Welcoming. The tea overall is ✨Immaculate✨

The person taking my order left their AirPods in and left me having to repeat my order several times. First they were about to ring up a completely different drink, they thought I wanted STRAWBERRY when I ordered wintermelon, as if those two words sound the same. I corrected them and thought it was okay after that, then I got some kind of yellow boba in my drink even though I asked them for black boba. I asked them why they put it in my drink suspecting they misheard me yet again from STILL NOT TAKING THE AIRPODS OUT and they told me “It tastes the same.” It did not taste the same, it had like a grassy, honey kind of taste. I’m giving two stars because the decor is SUPER PRETTY and I like the ambiance, for that reason alone I’ll likely try it again someday and update my review.
